com.castlabs.sdk.conviva

Class ConvivaAnalyticsSession

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.castlabs.sdk.conviva.ConvivaAnalyticsSession
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.castlabs.analytics.AnalyticsSession, com.castlabs.android.player.PlayerControllerPlugin.Component

    public class ConvivaAnalyticsSession
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.castlabs.analytics.AnalyticsSession

    This class allows to get full Conviva API access. You can get the Client instance with the getClient() method and the current session key with getSessionKey().

    To get the instance of this class use PlayerController.getComponent(Class) as follows: 

    
 ConvivaAnalyticsSession convivaAnalyticsSession = playerView.getPlayerController().getComponent(ConvivaAnalyticsSession.class);

    To send a custom Conviva event do the following: 

    
 if (convivaAnalyticsSession != null) {

     // Fill custom map
     Map<String, Object> customData = new HashMap<>();
     customData.put("now", Long.toString(System.currentTimeMillis()));
     customData.put("fizz", "buzz");

     int sessionKey = convivaAnalyticsSession.getSessionKey();
     String eventName = "customEvent";

     // Send event
     try {
         convivaAnalyticsSession.getClient().sendCustomEvent(sessionKey, eventName, customData);
     } catch (ConvivaException e) {
         Log.e("TAG", "Error while sending custom event");
         e.printStackTrace();
     }
}
